{"key":"processedPost-8902642","value":{"id":8902642,"first":8890757,"last":8902718,"when":1220995195,"utime":"09/10/08 12:19 AM","cleanedPost":"I do all work within a few inches at most from the face of the filter.&nbsp; Contaminants will fall from gravity into the air stream so get as close as you can.&nbsp; I recommend against sides and a top because they restrict your movement too much, especially with grain to grain transfers when you need to lift one jar over the other to pour the grains out.<br />If you want to see a flowhood in use, you can see video clips in the grain to grain transfer, petri dish prep, and master culture slant pages on <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">my website</a>.<br />RR"}}